This paper deals with the problem of detecting moving objects in videos, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves low-rank matrix decomposition and structured sparsity regularization, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of satellite videos, which suggests that it may fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) or information theory (cs.IT) due to the unique challenges posed by this type of data.
